#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:437
msgid ""
"We have a helper script which you can use to install all required external "
"dependencies:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:439
msgid "scripts\\install_deps.ps1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:443
msgid "This will install ``boost`` and ``cmake`` to the ``deps`` subdirectory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:446
msgid "Clone the Repository"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:448
msgid "To clone the source code, execute the following command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:450
msgid ""
"git clone --recursive https://github.com/argotorg/solidity.git\n"
"cd solidity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:455
msgid ""
"If you want to help develop Solidity, you should fork Solidity and add your "
"personal fork as a second remote:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:458
msgid "git remote add personal git@github.com:[username]/solidity.git"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:463
msgid ""
"This method will result in a pre-release build leading to e.g. a flag being "
"set in each bytecode produced by such a compiler. If you want to re-build a "
"released Solidity compiler, then please use the source tarball on the GitHub "
"release page:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:468
msgid ""
"https://github.com/argotorg/solidity/releases/download/v0.X.Y/solidity_0.X.Y."
"tar.gz"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:470
msgid "(not the \"Source code\" provided by GitHub)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:473
msgid "Command-Line Build"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:475
msgid "**Be sure to install External Dependencies (see above) before build.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:477
msgid ""
"Solidity project uses CMake to configure the build. You might want to "
"install `ccache`_ to speed up repeated builds. CMake will pick it up "
"automatically. Building Solidity is quite similar on Linux, macOS and other "
"Unices:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:484
msgid ""
"mkdir build\n"
"cd build\n"
"cmake .. && make"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:490
msgid "or even easier on Linux and macOS, you can run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:492
msgid ""
"#note: this will install binaries solc and soltest at usr/local/bin\n"
"./scripts/build.sh"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:499
msgid "BSD builds should work, but are untested by the Solidity team."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:501
msgid "And for Windows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:503
msgid ""
"mkdir build\n"
"cd build\n"
"cmake -G \"Visual Studio 16 2019\" .."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:509
msgid ""
"In case you want to use the version of boost installed by "
"``scripts\\install_deps.ps1``, you will additionally need to pass ``-"
"DBoost_ROOT=\"deps/boost\" -DBoost_INCLUDE_DIR=\"deps/boost/include\"`` and "
"``-DCMAKE_MSVC_RUNTIME_LIBRARY=MultiThreaded`` as arguments to the call to "
"``cmake``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:513
msgid ""
"This should result in the creation of **solidity.sln** in that build "
"directory. Double-clicking on that file should result in Visual Studio "
"firing up.  We suggest building **Release** configuration, but all others "
"work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:517
msgid "Alternatively, you can build for Windows on the command-line, like so:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:519
msgid "cmake --build . --config Release"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:524
msgid "CMake Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:526
msgid ""
"If you are interested what CMake options are available run ``cmake .. -LH``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:531
msgid "SMT Solvers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:532
msgid ""
"Solidity can optionally use SMT solvers, namely ``z3``, ``cvc5`` and "
"``Eldarica``, but their presence is checked only at runtime, they are not "
"needed for the build to succeed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:537
msgid ""
"The emscripten builds require Z3 and will statically link against it instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:540
msgid "The Version String in Detail"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:542
msgid "The Solidity version string contains four parts:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:544
msgid "the version number"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:545
msgid ""
"pre-release tag, usually set to ``develop.YYYY.MM.DD``, ``pre.N`` or "
"``nightly.YYYY.MM.DD``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:546
msgid "commit in the format of ``commit.GITHASH``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:547
msgid ""
"platform, which has an arbitrary number of items, containing details about "
"the platform and compiler"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:549
msgid ""
"If there are local modifications, the commit will be postfixed with ``.mod``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:551
msgid ""
"These parts are combined as required by SemVer, where the Solidity pre-"
"release tag equals to the SemVer pre-release and the Solidity commit and "
"platform combined make up the SemVer build metadata."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:554
msgid "Examples:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:556
msgid "release: ``0.4.8+commit.60cc1668.Emscripten.clang``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:557
msgid "pre-release: ``0.4.9-pre.3+commit.fb60450bc.Emscripten.clang``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:558
msgid ""
"nightly build: ``0.4.9-nightly.2017.1.17+commit.6ecb4aa3.Emscripten.clang``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:561
msgid "Important Information About Versioning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:563
msgid ""
"After a release is made, the patch version level is bumped, because we "
"assume that only patch level changes follow. When changes are merged, the "
"version should be bumped according to SemVer and the severity of the change. "
"Finally, a release is always made with the version of the current build, but "
"without the ``prerelease`` specifier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:568
msgid "Example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:570
msgid "The 0.4.0 release is made."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:571
msgid "Nightly builds and preerelases have a version of 0.4.1 from now on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:572
msgid "Non-breaking changes are introduced --> no change in version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:573
msgid "A breaking change is introduced --> version is bumped to 0.5.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:574
msgid "The 0.5.0 release is made."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../installing-solidity.rst:576
msgid ""
"This behavior works well with the :ref:`version pragma <version_pragma>`."
msgstr ""

